properties.headline: Flood Advisory issued January 12 at 5:30AM CST until January 13 at 5:25PM CST by NWS North Platte NE
properties.description:
...The National Weather Service in North Platte has issued a Flood
Advisory for the North Platte River...
North Platte River at Lewellen affecting Garden and Keith Counties

.Cold weather Saturday has caused an ice jam to form on the North Platte
river near Lewellen. The ice jam is expected to break up sometime in the
next few days.

The National Weather Service in North Platte has issued a
* Flood Advisory for
The North Platte River at Lewellen.
* until Monday afternoon.
* At  3:45 AM Sunday the stage was 8.1 feet.
* Flood stage is 8.0 feet.
* Forecast...The river will remain near 8.0 feet today and fall sometime
early this week.
* Impact...At 8.0 feet...Minor flood stage. Overflow and high water
table levels may cause seepage and flooding of basements and crawl
spaces near and along the river.
properties.instruction:
Stay tuned for further developments by listening to NOAA Weather
Radio, radio and television stations or online at
www.weather.gov/northplatte.
